<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">
    <body>
        <ol>
            <li>Make sure you are <a href="../../../../Central/Projects/Main-Activities/Associating-Users-Teams-Projects.htm" MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only" MadCap:excludeAction="unbind">associated with the project</a> for which you want to set up a site destination. Also, make sure the relevant <a href="../../../../Central/Projects/Page-Views/Builds/Main-Activities/Generating-Scheduling-Builds.htm" MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only" MadCap:excludeAction="unbind">target has at least one build successfully generated</a> for it.</li>
            <li>On the left side of the interface, click <b>Sites</b>.</li>
            <li>With the <span class="Emphasis">Sites</span> tab selected at the top, click <img src="../../../Images/Central/Interface/Buttons/Add-btn1.png" alt="" title="" class="ReduceButtonSize" />.</li>
            <li>On the <span class="Emphasis">Settings</span> tab of the dialog, complete the appropriate fields.<div class="topic-only"><ul><li><p><span class="Emphasis">Name </span>Give the site a name so that you easily recognize the output to which it points.</p><div class="example"><p class="Example-Text" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #242729;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Example &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;"> You might decide to name each site after a combination of the project and target names. If your project is called "Module 1" and the target is called "HTML5," you could name the site "Module 1 - HTML5."</p></div><div class="note"><p class="Note-Text" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #242729;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Note &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;">Keep in mind that the avatar automatically generated for the site will display the first three characters of the site's name.</p></div></li><li><span class="Emphasis">Domain </span>Select a domain (i.e., URL), which you create and manage in the URLs page view<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only"> (see <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Central/Sites/URLs-Page-View/URLs-Page-View.htm">URLs</MadCap:xref>)</MadCap:conditionalText>. If you are not mapping to your own host domain, just select the default Central domain.</li><li><p><span class="Emphasis">Vanity </span>(Optional) You can set a vanity for the output to produce a more meaningful URL that is easier to recognize when the site is live. This is also useful if you have multiple versions of a target's output and want to have a different URL for each version. If you do not provide a vanity here,  an auto-generated ID will be used. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Central/Sites/Sites-Page-View/Main-Activities/Setting-Site-Vanities.htm">Setting Site Vanities</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Print-Only">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Print-Only-Topics/Central/Sites/Setting-Site-Vanities.htm">Setting Site Vanities</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p><MadCap:snippetBlock src="../Projects/Note-Vanity-URL-Limitations.flsnp" /></li><li><span class="Emphasis">Site Theme </span>(Optional) Select a theme to use when displaying various interface elements (e.g., login fields, 404 pages) to end users<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only"> (see <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Central/Sites/Themes-Page-View/Creating-Themes.htm">Creating Themes</MadCap:xref>)</MadCap:conditionalText>. If you do not select a theme, the default Central design will be used.</li><li><span class="Emphasis">Site Trusted Domain Group </span>(Optional) Select a group containing domains that you want to allow in your output<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only"> (see <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Central/Sites/Security-Page-View/Adding-Trusted-Domain-Groups.htm">Adding Trusted Domain Groups</MadCap:xref> and <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Central/Sites/Security-Page-View/Adding-Trusted-Domains.htm">Adding Trusted Domains</MadCap:xref>)</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Print-Only"> (see <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Central/Sites/Security-Page-View/Adding-Trusted-Domain-Groups.htm">Adding Trusted Domain Groups</MadCap:xref> and <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Print-Only-Topics/Central/Sites/Adding-Trusted-Domains.htm">Adding Trusted Domains</MadCap:xref>)</MadCap:conditionalText>. For example, in one of your Flare topics maybe you have inserted a link to an external website within an IFrame. Without setting that domain as trusted, the site might fail to display due to certain security policies<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only"> (see <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Central/Server/Security.htm#SecurityHeadersTrustedDomains">Security Headers and Trusted Domains</MadCap:xref>)</MadCap:conditionalText>.</li><li><p><span class="Emphasis">Build </span>Select a destination (i.e., output) for the site. From the drop-down, first select a project, then a target, and finally a build. You can select a specific build (based on the build's completion date and time), or you can select <span class="Emphasis">Latest Build</span> (i.e., the most recent successful build will be used automatically).</p><div class="warning"><p class="Warning-Text" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #242729;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Warning &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;">If you are setting the site as "live" for the general public, we recommend you select a specific build. Otherwise, if you tell Central to use the latest build, you might end up with live output that is not yet ready for publication but happens to be the most recent build for the target. However, if the output is also set as "private" and intended only for individuals in your company, you might find it beneficial to choose the latest build. Just give it some thought when making a selection in this field.</p></div><div class="tip"><p class="Tip-Text" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #242729;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Tip &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;">If this is a site where the build might be updated over time, it is a good idea to set the previously live build to "keep," just in case you need to roll back to it at some point. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Central/Projects/Page-Views/Builds/Other-Activities/Setting-Builds-Keep.htm">Setting Builds as Keep</MadCap:xref> and <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Central/Sites/Sites-Page-View/Main-Activities/Rolling-Back-Previous-Live-Output.htm">Rolling Back to a Previous Live Output</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Print-Only">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Print-Only-Topics/Central/Sites/Rolling-Back-Previous-Live-Output.htm">Rolling Back to a Previous Live Output</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p></div></li><li><span class="Emphasis">Set live </span>(Optional) <MadCap:snippetText src="Set-Live-Summary.flsnp" /> <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Central/Sites/Sites-Page-View/Main-Activities/Setting-Sites-Live.htm">Setting Sites as Live</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Print-Only">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Print-Only-Topics/Central/Sites/Setting-Sites-Live.htm">Setting Sites as Live</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></li><li><p><span class="Emphasis">Include in search engines </span>(Optional) <MadCap:snippetText src="../Projects/Exclude-Live-Builds-Search.flsnp" /> <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Central/Sites/Sites-Page-View/Other-Activities/Excluding-Sites-Search-Engines.htm">Excluding Live Sites From Search Engines</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Print-Only"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Print-Only-Topics/Central/Sites/Excluding-Sites-Search-Engines.htm">Excluding Live Sites From Search Engines</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p><div class="note"><p class="Note-Text" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #242729;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Note &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;"><MadCap:snippetText src="../Projects/Exclude-Live-Builds-Search2.flsnp" /></p></div></li><li><span class="Emphasis">Set private </span>(Optional) You can set HTML5 outputs as "private." Users must log in to view the output, which means they must be part of your license as authors, SMEs, or viewers. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Central/Sites/Sites-Page-View/Main-Activities/Setting-Sites-Private.htm">Setting Sites as Private</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Print-Only">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Print-Only-Topics/Central/Sites/Setting-Sites-Private.htm">Setting Sites as Private</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></li></ul></div></li>
            <li>(Optional) Click the <span class="Emphasis">Teams</span> tab, and select the team(s) to associate with the site. The primary reason for doing this is to make private output available to users. A user must be on a team that is associated with a private site in order to view the output.</li>
            <li>Click <span class="Emphasis">Save</span>.</li>
        </ol>
    </body>
</html>